quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  33,55,"There is no objection to their [appearing before] their fathers, their sons nor their brothers, nor their brothers' and sisters' sons, nor their [Muslim] womenfolk, nor anyone their right hands control [of female slaves]. Heed Allah (God) (you women); Allah (God) is a Witness for everything!"
  33,56,"Allah (God) and His angels bless the Prophet. You who believe, pray for him (too) and greet him properly."
  33,57,"Allah (God) will curse those who [try to] annoy Allah (God) and His messenger in this world and the Hereafter, and will prepare shameful torment for them."
  33,58,"Those who annoy believing men and believing women without their having deserved it, will assume [the guilt of] slander and [commit] a clear offence against themselves."
  33,59,"O Prophet, tell your wives and daughters, and believers' wives as well, to draw their cloaks close around themselves. That is more appropriate so they may be recognized and not molested. Allah (God) is Forgiving, Merciful."
  33,60,"If hypocrites and those whose hearts contain malice do not stop, as well as the agitators in Madina, We shall stir you up against them. Then they will live alongside you as neighbors for only a little while [longer];"
  33,61,"cursed wherever they are encountered, they will be seized and completely killed."
  33,62,"[Such is] Allah (God)'s practice with those who have passed on before; you will never find any change in Allah (God)'s practice."